“RESPECT MY EXISTANCE OR EXPECT MY RESISTANCE”

Trans Day of Visibility is an annual celebration to raise awareness about trans people and the discrimination they face. Republican led states have passed numerous anti-trans laws to prohibit trans people from participating in sports, using bathrooms, receiving healthcare, education, legal recognition, and the right to exist. It seems as though Republicans are more concerned with banning drag shows than military assault rifles, which continues to be the number one cause of death in children. On this Trans Day of Visibility, youth organizers led a rally in Union Square and marched to Washington Square Park.

Do the “write” thing!

The Writers Guild of America (WGA) is currently on strike after they failed to reach a deal with the Alliance of Motion Picture and Television Producers (AMPTP). The WGA claims that AMPTP’s share of residuals from streaming media has cut much of writers’ average incomes. There is also concern that artificial intelligence will replace many writers. Our beloved television shows are on halt for the foreseeable future while writers continue striking for what may be a significant amount of time; no prospect of a deal has been made with AMPTP. 

@wgaeast union members held a large picket at the offices of HBO and Amazon in Hudson Yards, New York. There was also picket lines in Chelsea for the show “Billions” that is currently in production.
